# VM SSH MCP – Cross-Platform VM Access (All Agents)

## Purpose

When Claude Code, Claude Cowork, or Cursor needs to run commands on VMs, upload/download files, or check connectivity, use the **mycosoft-ssh** MCP server.

## When to Use

- Run commands on sandbox, MAS, MINDEX, GPU, or MYCA VMs
- Upload files (e.g. deploy scripts, configs) to VMs
- Download logs or configs from VMs
- Check VM SSH connectivity before deployments

## Tools (MCP mycosoft-ssh)

| Tool | Example |
|------|---------|
| `ssh_exec` | `ssh_exec(host="mas", command="docker ps")` |
| `ssh_exec` (sudo) | `ssh_exec(host="sandbox", command="systemctl restart docker", sudo=True)` |
| `ssh_upload` | `ssh_upload(host="myca", local_path="./config.env", remote_path="/opt/myca/config.env")` |
| `ssh_download` | `ssh_download(host="mindex", remote_path="/var/log/mindex.log")` |
| `ssh_status` | `ssh_status()` — connectivity check for all 5 VMs |

## Host Aliases

- `sandbox` → 192.168.0.187  
- `mas` → 192.168.0.188  
- `mindex` → 192.168.0.189  
- `gpu` → 192.168.0.190  
- `myca` → 192.168.0.191  

## Cursor Fallback

If the mycosoft-ssh MCP is not available in Cursor, use existing patterns:

- Load credentials from `.credentials.local`
- Use Python scripts (e.g. `scripts/deploy-mas.ps1`, `_deploy_sandbox.py`) that SSH via paramiko
- Follow `agent-must-execute-operations.mdc` — agents execute deploy/SSH themselves

## Adding New VMs

Add to `mcp/mycosoft_ssh/server.py` in `VM_HOSTS`. Only `192.168.0.x` IPs are allowed. See `docs/MYCOSOFT_SSH_MCP_MAR03_2026.md`.

